1. DokuWiki: This wiki software doesn't require a database to use and is highly suitable for smaller businesses. There's a mobile-friendly interface, making it easy to use on phones.

2. MediaWiki: It's the software behind the famous Wikipedia and several other wiki websites. It's also mobile-friendly.

3. Tiki Wiki: This full-feature web-based wiki software has an in-built mobile support version, a clean interface, and good performance on phones.

4. Foswiki: Although a little tech-heavy, Foswiki also has a decent mobile interface.

5. BookStack: It's a simple, self-hosted, and easy-to-use platform. BookStack has a clean, straightforward, and responsive design that looks great on mobile.

6. XWiki: It offers a powerful wiki platform with a lot of extensibility features. The software has responsive design and works well on mobile devices.

7. Wiki.js: A modern wiki software that features a sleek, responsive layout and a rich content editor. It renders well on mobile devices.

Remember to do a bit of research about these packages, so you can choose the one that best suits your needs.
