After Data Preprocessing and Visualization, I have tried to build the model :


[](https://i.stack.imgur.com/6j7kt.png)
Please help with the error
<|end|>
<|asst|>
The error you're receiving is because you're trying to use a classification metric (like accuracy_score) on a regression problem. 

Classification and regression problems are different:

* Classification: with outcome variables taking the form of labels (discrete categories).
* Regression: with outcome variables taking the form of continuous values.

Random Forest can be used for both regression and classification but the nature of the target variable decides the evaluation metrics. In your case, since the problem is a regression one, you can't use accuracy as a metric.

Instead of accuracy, regression problems typically use metrics like:

- Mean Squared Error (MSE)
- Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE)
- Mean Absolute Error (MAE)
- R Squared (R^2 or Coefficient of determination)

For instance, using Mean Absolute Error in scikit-learn:
```python
from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error
y_true = ...
y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
print(mean_absolute_error(y_true, y_pred))
```

On a side note, when you're doing train/test split make sure you're not using test data in your model training phase. It seems from the code that you have concatenated train and test datasets. This violates the general rule of machine learning where a model should never be trained on testing data.
<|end|>


