Craft a JavaScript function that outputs the sequence of Fibonacci numbers up until the nth term, where n is a defined variable. The Fibonacci series should be calculated using a recursive algorithm, outputted as an array.

Constraints:
- You are not allowed to use global or static variables.
- The function should be able to handle a range of 'n' up to 30.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is the JavaScript function to generate Fibonacci numbers up to the nth term using a recursive algorithm:

```javascript
function fibonacci(n) {
    if (n === 0) {
        return [0];
    } else if (n == 1) {
        return [0, 1];
    } else {
        let s = fibonacci(n - 1);
        s.push(s[s.length - 1] + s[s.length - 2]);
        return s;
    }
}

console.log(fibonacci(30));
```

'N' is the defined variable which indicates up to which term the Fibonacci sequence will be generated. This function works by finding the Fibonacci numbers of 'n - 1' and then appending the next number to the end of the array. The Fibonacci numbers for 'n - 1' are found by recursively calling the function with smaller values of 'n', until the base case is reached where 'n' is 1 or 0. The function then returns an array with the Fibonacci number sequence up to the nth term.

Please note that, the function has a time complexity of approximately O(2^n), and it may not perform well for larger values of 'n' due to the stack overflow during the recursive calls. But as per the constraints, this function will work accurately and efficiently for 'n' up to 30.
