Compose an SQL command in order to procure the average performance metrics from the lowest ranking quintuple participants out of a database table maintaining a record of points procured by all contenders.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Assuming that we have a table named 'Contest' with two columns: 'Participant' and 'Points', where 'Participant' is the name of each participant and 'Points' are points procured by each participant. Here is one way this problem can be solved:

```sql
SELECT AVG(Points) AS AvgLowestPoints
FROM 
  (SELECT Points
   FROM Contest
   ORDER BY Points ASC
   LIMIT 5) AS LowestFive
```
This query works by creating a subquery (due to the parentheses) that selects the 'Points' of all participants, sorts them in ascending order (so, from lowest to highest), and then limits the results to just the first five, which will be the lowest-ranking quintuple participants.

The outer query then takes the average of these 'Points' from the subquery. The AS keyword is just used to give a more descriptive name ('AverageLowestPoints') to this number returned by the query.
<|end|>


