Develop a Java program that not only determines if a given String input represents a palindrome (ignoring special characters, white spaces, and case sensitivity), but also finds the longest palindromic substring within it. The program should also print out the longest palindromic substring.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is a Java solution for the problem:

```java
public class Main {

    public static String longestPalindromicSubstring(String s) {
        if (s == null || s.length() == 0)
            return "";
        
        int start = 0, end = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            int len1 = expandAroundCenter(s, i, i);
            int len2 = expandAroundCenter(s, i, i + 1);
            int len = Math.max(len1, len2);
            if (len > end - start) {
                start = i - (len - 1) / 2;
                end = i + len / 2;
            }
        }
        return s.substring(start, end + 1);
    }

    private static int expandAroundCenter(String s, int left, int right) {
        int L = left, R = right;
        while (L >= 0 && R < s.length() && s.charAt(L) == s.charAt(R)) {
            L--;
            R++;
        }
        return R - L - 1;
    }

    public static boolean isPalindrome(String str) {
        String cleanStr = str.replaceAll("\\W", "").toLowerCase();
        StringBuilder s = new StringBuilder(cleanStr);
        String reverse = s.reverse().toString();

        return reverse.equals(cleanStr);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String test = "Madam Arora teaches malayalam";
        System.out.println("Is palindrome? " + isPalindrome(test));
        System.out.println("Longest Palindromic Substring: " + longestPalindromicSubstring(test));
    }
}
```
In the code above, the `main` method firstly determines if the input string is a palindrome, and then finds the longest palindromic substring. The input string `test` has been initialized as "Madam Arora teaches malayalam". 

The `isPalindrome` method cleans the string by removing white spaces, special characters and making it case insensitive. Then the string is reversed to check if it is same as the original string. The `longestPalindromicSubstring` method uses the expand around center approach to find the longest palindrome. The `expandAroundCenter` helper function increases the left and right pointer if the characters at the left and right are the same.
