Below is a Java code of a `StudentScoreCard` class that includes methods for adding new grade and calculating the mean score.

```java
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public class StudentScoreCard {
    // List to store the grades of the student.
    private List<Integer> grades = new ArrayList<>();

    // Method to add a new grade to the student's scorecard.
    public void addGrade(int grade){
        grades.add(grade);
    }

    // Method to calculate the mean of the student's grades.
    public double calculateMean(){
        double sum = 0;
        for(int grade : grades){
            sum += grade;
        }
        return grades.size() > 0 ? sum / grades.size() : 0;
    }
}
```
This class uses an `ArrayList` to store the grades for a student. It provides `addGrade(int grade)` method to add a new grade to the list, and `calculateMean()` method to compute the mean of the stored grades. The `calculateMean()` method sums all the grades and then divides it by the total number of grades to obtain the mean.

You can use this class in your code like this:

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Create a StudentScoreCard object.
        StudentScoreCard scoreCard = new StudentScoreCard();

        // Add grades to the scorecard.
        scoreCard.addGrade(75);
        scoreCard.addGrade(85);
        scoreCard.addGrade(90);

        // Calculate and print the mean of the grades.
        System.out.println("Mean score: " + scoreCard.calculateMean());
    }
}
```
