The `SpecialCells` method throws an exception if no cells matching the specified criteria are found. Since it's calling a COM method, the exception isn't handled the usual way, which leads to this cryptic exception.

You can avoid this by first checking whether there are any cells matching the criteria in the range before calling `SpecialCells`:

```
Excel.Worksheet myWs = (Excel.Worksheet)ModelWb.Worksheets[1];
