It seems you want to transpose your dataframe and convert column names into a row with 'Name' column being transposed as column headers. You can achieve this in pandas using the `transpose()` function and following some additional steps:

```python
import pandas as pd

# Read the data
map_df = pd.read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/GeorgeRobbin/GeorgeRobbin.github.io/main/Delinnquency_MAP.csv')

# Transpose the dataframe
df_transpose = map_df.set_index('Name').transpose()

# Reset the index
df_final = df_transpose.reset_index().rename(columns={'index':'date'})
```

You can then access your desired format in `df_final`.

