<|end|>
<|asst|>
In order to update the email address of a specific member in the "users" collection, you can use the `updateOne()` method in MongoDB. Here's how the command might look:

```javascript
db.users.updateOne(
   { "username": "JohnDoe" },
   { 
     $set: { "email": "newemail@example.com" } 
   }
)
```
In this command:
1. `"username": "JohnDoe"` is used to find the document (or the member, in this context) with the username `"JohnDoe"`.
2. `$set: { "email": "newemail@example.com" }` modifies the email field of the found document to `"newemail@example.com"`. 

It's important to point out that `updateOne()` will only update the first document that matches the provided query. If there are potentially multiple documents that could match the query, and you intended to update all of them, you would want to use `updateMany()` instead.
