This is because the log return of 1/X will not linearly correspond to the log return of X. The correlation between the log of two random variables X and Y depends on the joint distribution of the two random variables, and this relationship will be affected when calculating the log of 1/X. The log-returns are calculated as the logarithm of the ratio of consecutive prices, and taking the inverse of the price will necessarily alter these ratios.

Therefore, to accurately determine the correlation between the log-returns of 1/X and Y, you would need to calculate this directly from the data of 1/X and Y.
