Converting this script into C code isn't straightforward because Spark isn't directly supported in C, it is in Java, Scala, Python, and R. The CSV I/O and operations on dataframe are conceptually different in C and Spark (Python) due to the different levels of abstraction and different computational models (procedural in C vs data parallel in Spark). 

However, as C has CSV libraries, you can read the CSV file and perform some operations. For doing any distributed computation, MPI or OpenMP like libraries can be used. 

