```
Please note this is not an equivalent C program for your Spark code. The differences in computation model between C and Spark make such conversion impractical and inefficient. The equivalent operations in C would require building your own data model and join operation, which is exactly what dataframe-based systems like Spark were designed to abstract away from the programmer. 

For developing similar Big Data processing programs in C, consider using Apache Arrow, which allows you to work with big data but requires a lot more groundwork and lacks the higher-level operations provided by Spark. 

For distributed computing, MPI (Message Passing Interface) or OpenMP can be used but it requires advanced knowledge in Parallel Computing and could become a challenging task. 

In general, languages like Python with Spark, pandas and other libraries that abstract away the complexities of Big Data processing, are recommended.
