I'm trying to write a custom WPF ValidationRule to enforce that a certain property is unique within the context of a given collection. For example: I am editing a collection of custom objects bound to a ListView and I need to ensure that the Name property of each object in the collection is unique. Does anyone know how to do this?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
You can use a `ValidationRule` to enforce the uniqueness of a particular property among a collection of items in WPF. Here's an example on how to make sure that a `Name` property remains unique within a bound collection.

Since `ValidationRule` inherits from `DependencyObject`, it cannot be bound to an actual value, so you will have to update the property value of the rule whenever the collection changes.

```csharp
public class UniqueNameRule : ValidationRule
{
    public ObservableCollection<MyObject> Collection { get; set; }

    public override ValidationResult Validate(object value, CultureInfo cultureInfo)
    {
        string name = (string)value;
        int count = Collection.Count(x => x.Name == name);
        if (count > 1)
        {
            return new ValidationResult(false, $"{name} is not unique.");
        }
        return ValidationResult.ValidResult;
    }
}
```

Apply the rule to the `TextBox`you want to validate:

```xaml
<TextBox>
    <TextBox.Text>
        <Binding Path="Name" UpdateSourceTrigger="PropertyChanged">
            <Binding.ValidationRules>
                <local:UniqueNameRule Collection="{Binding MyObjectsCollection}" />
            </Binding.ValidationRules>
        </Binding>
    </TextBox.Text>
</TextBox>
```

Remember to set `UpdateSourceTrigger="PropertyChanged"` to make sure the validation rule is checked each time you modify the `TextBox`.

And make sure to update the `Collection` in your `UniqueNameRule` whenever your actual collection changes.

Note:

The above example assumes that you have an `ObservableCollection` of objects of type `MyObject` and `MyObject` has a property of type string called `Name`. Replace `MyObject` and `Name` with your actual class and property names.

Also, this rule only checks if the `name` is unique when you lose focus from the `TextBox`. If you want to check for uniqueness as soon as you type, you need to use a different approach like creating a validation logic in view model itself.
<|end|>


