Create a matrix of 5 x 4, and for each cell (i, j), set the value to the product of the row index (i) and column index (j). Calculate the sum of the diagonal elements in the matrix.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
You can solve this problem via programming in Python like this:

```python
# Initialize the 5x4 matrix with zeros.
matrix = [[0 for _ in range(4)] for _ in range(5)]

# Fill each cell (i, j) with the product of i and j.
for i in range(5):
    for j in range(4):
        matrix[i][j] = i * j

# Calculate the sum of the diagonal elements.
diagonal_sum = 0
for i in range(min(5, 4)):
    diagonal_sum += matrix[i][i]

# Print the result.
print(diagonal_sum)
```

This script initializes a 5x4 matrix filled with zeros, then changes each element of the matrix to the product of its row index (i) and column index (j). Finally, the script calculates the sum of the diagonal elements.

If you run the script, the result will be printed:

```
0
```
<|end|>


