Changing a value prompt to a multi-select value prompt in Report studio, provide single select functionality. How can i get multi-select functionality?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
To get a multi-select functionality in IBM's Cognos Report studio, you need to do more than just changing a value prompt to a multi-select value prompt, as the report's query also has to be adjusted.

Here's how you can do it:

1. First, change the prompt type: Go to the 'Insert-able Objects' pane, drag a 'Value Prompt' into your prompt page, and in the properties pane, set 'Select UI' property to 'Multi-select'.

2. Modify report's query: Go to Query Explorer and open your query. Here you need to make sure, it is capable of handling multi-value prompts. The expression should be changed from `[DataSet].[Field] = ?prompt?` to `[DataSet].[Field] in (?prompt?)`.

3. Run the report: Now when you run the report, the prompt page displays a multi-select list box where you can select multiple values simultaneously.

Remember the part `[DataSet].[Field] in (?prompt?)` is very important, without this the prompt will not be able to accept multiple values.
<|end|>


