<|asst|>
Here's the converted PHP code. I've included comments that explain each part of the code.

```php
<?php
// Function to check for even length and no digit in the string
function check($item) {
    $digitCheck = preg_match('/\d/', $item);
    return strlen($item) % 2 == 0 && !$digitCheck;
}

// Function to sort by length then by case-insensitive value
function sort_criteria($a, $b)
{
    if(strlen($a) == strlen($b)) {
        return strcasecmp($a, $b);
    }
    return (strlen($a) < strlen($b)) ? -1 : 1;
}

function sorted_list_sum($list, $reverse = FALSE) {
    // Filter the array using the check function
    $list = array_filter($list, "check");

    // Use usort to custom sort the array
    usort($list, "sort_criteria");
    
    // If reverse is true, reverse the order of the array
    if($reverse) $list = array_reverse($list);

    return $list;
}

?>
```

To breakdown each part:

- A helper function `check($item)` has been defined, to check each item in the list is even in length and does not have any numeric digit.
- A custom sort function `sort_criteria($a, $b)` is written to sort the array by length, and then by string comparison.
- usort() function is used with 'sort_criteria' to sort the array based on custom criteria.
- We also use strcasecmp() PHP function to sort strings in a case-insensitive way.
- array_reverse() is used to reverse the order of the list if $reverse is true.
- array_filter() is used along with our helper function 'check' to filter the array.
<|end|>


