Here is a JavaScript code snippet that can handle what you are asking.

```javascript
let myArray = [1,2,3,[4,5]];

function getFirstElement(arr){
    let firstElement = arr[0];
    
    // Check if the first element itself is an array
    if(Array.isArray(firstElement)) {
        // If it is an array, call the same function recursively
        return getFirstElement(firstElement);
    }
    else {
        // If it is not an array, return the element
        return firstElement;
    }
}

console.log(getFirstElement(myArray));  // Output should be 1
```

This function uses a recursive approach where it checks if the first element of the given array is itself an array. If it is, it calls the function again on that array. If the first element is not an array, it simply returns that element. 

This will continue until it hits a non-array element, which will then be returned as the first non-array element of the nested structure.

