This error is due to Angular trying to resolve 'util' which is a native node.js module that's not available in the Angular browser environment.

Firstly, you want to make sure there are no NodeJS dependencies in your Angular project. If you have any, move them away, preferably you would want to have a shared library that doesn't contain any platform-specific imports.

If you're certain no such dependencies are in your project and the error still persist then you might want to consider clearing your node modules. Remove node_modules folder and package-lock.json file (if exists) then do a fresh install:

```bash
rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
npm install
```
If you are using yarn, delete yarn.lock file and node_modules folder and then run 'yarn install'.

Remember, the best way to share code (like interfaces, DTOs, utility functions) between frontend(Angular) and backend(NestJS) in a monorepot setup, is to put the shared code inside a separate library, which has no dependencies on node-specific or browser-specific libraries. This way, you can import from the shared lib in both NestJS and Angular sides, without running into these platform-specific issues.
