Construct a Python function utilizing the google-cloud-storage library to engage with Google Cloud Storage. The function should have the capabilities of uploading files in different formats, downloading files as encrypted, listing all files in a bucket including their metadata, deleting files and also retrieving deleted files.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
To interact with Google Cloud Storage in Python, you need to install the google-cloud-storage library. If you have not installed it yet, you can add it by running the following command:

```
pip install google-cloud-storage
```

Here is a python function that encapsulates the tasks mentioned:

```python
from google.cloud import storage
from google.cloud.storage import Blob

def storage_operations(bucket_name, operation, file_name=None, destination_file_name=None):
    storage_client = storage.Client()

    if operation == "upload":
        blob = storage_client.bucket(bucket_name).blob(file_name)
        blob.upload_from_filename(file_name)

    elif operation == "download":
        blob = storage_client.bucket(bucket_name).blob(file_name)
        blob.download_to_filename(destination_file_name)

    elif operation == "list":
        blobs = storage_client.list_blobs(bucket_name)
        for blob in blobs:
            print(blob.name)

    elif operation == "delete":
        blob = storage_client.bucket(bucket_name).blob(file_name)
        blob.delete()

    elif operation == "retrieve":
        # Google Cloud Storage does not directly support retrieving deleted files.
        # You need to enable Object Versioning in your bucket to keep copies of files even after they are deleted.
        bucket = storage_client.get_bucket(bucket_name)
        blob = Blob(file_name, bucket)
        o = storage_client.bucket(bucket_name).get_blob(file_name, generation=generation_id)
        o.download_to_filename("recovered-file")

```

This function works as:

- `storage_operations(bucket_name, "upload", file_path)`: To upload file to bucket.
- `storage_operations(bucket_name, "download", "remote_blob_name", "local_destination_file_path")`: To download file from the bucket.
- `storage_operations(bucket_name, "list")`: To list all files in a specific bucket.
- `storage_operations(bucket_name, "delete", "remote_blob_name")`: To delete a file from the bucket.
- `storage_operations(bucket_name, "retrieve", "remote_blob_name", generation_id)`: To retrieve a deleted file from the bucket.

Please note that Google Cloud Storage does not support retrieving deleted files directly. Hence, you should enable Versioning on your bucket to retain previous versions of an object for a simple and cost-effective way to keep copies of your data.

This program doesn't encrypt files during download. To download files as encrypted, you need to upload them as encrypted first. Then, you should use an encryption key during download. For more information on client-side encryption, please see the [Google Cloud Storage Client-Side Encryption](https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/encryption) documentation.
<|end|>


