System Genesis:

We could adopt a hybrid architecture that incorporates permissioned and permissionless nodes, fused with a multi-agency model to reduce the reliance on a single entity controlling the transactions. The system could be founded using a comprehensive Proof of Stake (PoS) for mining, which offers effective security, reduced power consumption, and a decentralized trust system. 

Programming Language:

Python could be the primary language for developing this DLT system due to its simplicity, versatility, and extensive library support for deep learning and blockchain technologies. Whether it’s creating smart contracts, ensuring cryptographic security, or designing the deep learning models, Python provides the efficiency and speed needed in a high-stake environment like financial transactions.

Deep Learning Model:

A Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) could be incorporated into the architecture to enhance efficiency. The CNN will analyze patterns and features in the distributed ledger data, providing real-time supervision of network activities. Possible malicious activities and other security vulnerabilities can be identified and mitigated before they escalate into severe issues. Further, a Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) can improve the execution speed by learning the sequence of transactions and predicting the next transactions.

Implications on Network Scalability & User Anonymity:

A hybrid structure will allow for scalability by permissioned nodes handling the bulk of transactions and permissionless nodes maintaining decentralization. To ensure user anonymity, a ring signature or zero-knowledge proofs could be implemented, enabling the users to prove knowledge of a secret without divulging the secret itself.

Impact on Contract Execution Speed & Financial Feasibility:

Utilizing deep learning models could significantly enhance the speed of executing smart contracts since CNN and RNN will effectively align the transactional data, reducing computational burdens. Although initial implementation costs are high due to the advanced AI technology, the potential benefits of sophisticated AI security measures, improved transaction speed, and reduced need for intermediaries, can facilitate a cost-effective solution in the long run. 

Prospects for Future Expansion:

The hybrid approach, coupled with the chosen deep learning model, provides flexibility and allows the proposed DLT system to adapt to future advancements in technology comfortably. Python also ensures compatibility with potential future upgrades, considering its dynamic nature and active open-source community. 

Overall, the proposed DLT system leverages AI technology in a sophisticated, cost-effective, secure, and highly scalable way. By merging DL models with blockchain technology, the system not only ensures a significant reduction in vulnerabilities but also optimizes smart contract execution and ensures a scalable and efficient system.
