Block 1: Hierarchical Dropdown Menu using CSS 

```css
ul {
  list-style-type: none;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
  background-color: #333;
}

li {
  float: left;
}

li a, .dropButton {
  display: inline-block;
  color: white;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 14px 16px;
  text-decoration: none;
}

li a:hover, .dropdown:hover .dropButton {
  background-color: red;
}

li.dropdown {
  display: inline-block;
}

.dropdown-content {
  display: none;
  position: absolute;
  background-color: #f9f9f9;
  min-width: 160px;
  box-shadow: 0px 8px 16px 0px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
}

.dropdown-content a {
  color: black;
  padding: 12px 16px;
  text-decoration: none;
  display: block;
  text-align: left;
}

.dropdown-content a:hover {background-color: #f1f1f1}

.dropdown:hover .dropdown-content {
  display: block;
}
```

Block 2: Dynamic Image Collection using CSS Grid & Flexbox

```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
  grid-gap: 10px;
  padding: 10px;
}

.image-card {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  margin: 10px;
  height: 300px;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 8px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
}

.image-card img {
  width: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  height: 200px;
}

.image-card p {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 10px;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
  overflow: hidden;
  white-space: nowrap;
}

/* For devices with smaller width */
@media all and (max-width: 500px) {
  .container {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(100px, 1fr));
  }

  .image-card {
    height: 200px;
  }

  .image-card img {
    height: 100px;
  }
}
```
This code block demonstrates an image gallery, organized as a grid of cards. Each card contains the image and a caption. The gallery is responsively designed to adapt to different device sizes using media queries. The number, size, and orientation of the cards adjust according to the available space.
<|end|>


