<|asst|>
To code a custom technical indicator in Pine script, follow the steps below:

1. Go to "TradingView" and log into your account.

2. Click on the "Pine Editor" tab at the bottom set of tabs. This will open your pine editor environment where you can write your script.

Here is a simple example: A custom SMA (Simple Moving Average) indicator. It calculates the average price for the last 'n' periods.

```pinescript
//@version=4
study("My_SMA_Script", overlay = true)

length = input(14, minval = 1)              //Input for moving average window /period
src = close                                 //The source of our data, here being the closing price

sma = 0.0                                   //Define a variable 'sma'

sma := sma(src, length)                     //Compute the simple moving average
plot(sma)

```
In this script, "study" function defines the properties of the script. The "input" function defines the length of the moving average (default is 14). The source of our data, "src", is the close prices. Calculations of the simple moving average is done using "sma()" function and it is stored in the "sma" variable. The result is then plotted on your chart with the "plot" function.

3. After writing the script, click "Add to Chart" button to view it on your chart.

Please note that this is a simple script for illustrative purposes. A more complex technical indicator will require additional functions and logic.

**NB:** Always remember to check your script for any syntax errors, logical errors before adding to the chart.

Also, it's essential to understand that Pine Script is limited to the functionalities provided by TradingView and it's quite different from the standard programming languages. Hence, loading external data, performing file I/O operations, using third-party libraries, etc. are not possible in Pine Script.

For more complex tasks, you may need to learn more about built-in functions, data types and other components of the Pine Script language by visiting its documentation or by exploring example scripts on TradingView.
<|end|>


