<|asst|>
This is a Python example which uses the built-in sum function to quickly sum up the elements in the list.

```python
from typing import List

def compute_difference(set1: List[int], set2: List[int]) -> int:
    return abs(sum(set1) - sum(set2))
```

Here, the sum function computes the sum of the elements in the input list. This function has a complexity of O(n), since each element of the list must be visited once. 

The difference between the sums is then computed, and the absolute value of this difference is returned. The abs function, subtraction operation, and the return statement all have a complexity of O(1), so they don't affect the overall time complexity of the function.

Therefore, the total time complexity of the function is O(n).
<|end|>


