Is there a simple way to extract the next earning date into a google spreadsheet from a website or using googlefinance()? I want a google sheet formula which will output the next quarterly or yearly earnings date. I found nothing yet.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Unfortunately, there isn't a built-in googlefinance() function to pull future earnings date data in Google Sheets. GoogleFinance does not support such a capability and that's probably due to the fact that earnings dates can often be subject to change.

There are ways to pull such data by building a custom function using Apps Script or pulling it from an API that provides forward-looking earning dates such as IEX Cloud, Alpha Vantage, or any other financial data API service. However, these methods require knowledge of JavaScript/Coding and API integration.

Before doing so, you need to make sure the terms of service for your chosen data provider permit this type of use. You should note that this data might not be 100% reliable as sometimes companies change their earnings call dates.

Here's a sample custom function using Apps Script:

```javascript
function getNextEarningsDate(symbol) {
  var url = 'https://www.alphavantage.co/query?function=EARNINGS&symbol=' + symbol + '&apikey=demo';
  var response = UrlFetchApp.fetch(url);
  var json = response.getContentText();
  var data = JSON.parse(json);

  if (data['quarterlyEarnings']) {
    for (var i = 0; i < data['quarterlyEarnings'].length; i++) {
      if (new Date(data['quarterlyEarnings'][0]['fiscalDateEnding']) > new Date()) {
        return data['quarterlyEarnings'][0]['fiscalDateEnding'];
      }
    }
  }
  return 'No upcoming earnings date found';
}
```

In this code, replace "demo" in the url with your own API Key from AlphaVantage.

Once the custom function is added to your Google Sheets Script Editor, you can call it in your sheet with `=getNextEarningsDate('AMZN')`, replacing 'AMZN' with any stock symbol that you want.

Remember, you'll need to sign up and fetch API key from Alpha Vantage (or any other financial data provider which provides future earnings date) and replace 'demo' with your key.

Please keep in mind that this method is not simple and might not be suitable for individuals without technical experience. Therefore, most people usually just manually look up the next earnings date or get it from a finance news outlet.
<|end|>


