Create a function to convert a string to a secret string in Java.
String : "This is a test"
<|end|>
<|asst|>
You can create a function which converts all the letters to their ASCII value and all the spaces to underscore symbols to make the string unreadable. It's a very basic form of string encryption but can work for very simple scenarios. Here is how you can implement it:

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(convertToSecret("This is a test"));
    }

    public static String convertToSecret(String str) {
        StringBuilder secret = new StringBuilder();
        for (char c : str.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == ' ') {
                secret.append('_');
            } else {
                secret.append((int) c);
            }
        }
        return secret.toString();
    }
}
```

This `convertToSecret` function converts every character to its ASCII value, and spaces are converted to underscore symbols. Please note that encoded string will only consist of ASCII decimal values and underscores so it's not readable anymore.

For example, the string "This is a test" will become "84105115115_105115_97105_116101115116".
<|end|>


