<body>
    <div><head>My Website</head></div>
</body>
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is the fixed markup syntax as per HTML5 standards:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My Website</title>
</head>
<body>
    <div>My Website</div>
</body>
</html>
```
Explanation:
- HTML documents should start with `<!DOCTYPE html>` declaration to define it is an HTML5 document.
- `<html>` tag is the root of an HTML page.
- `<head>` tag is a container for metadata (data about data) and is placed between the `<html>` tag and the `<body>` tag. Metadata is data about the HTML document. Metadata is not displayed.
- `<title>` (inside head tag) - Defines a title for the document
- `<body>` tag is the container for all the visible contents, such as headings, paragraphs, images, hyperlinks, tables, lists, etc.
- `<div>` tag is nothing more than a container unit that encapsulates other page elements and divides the HTML document into sections. Web developers use `<div>` elements to group together HTML elements and apply CSS styles to many elements at once.

Note: `<head>` tag is not supposed to be inside `<body>` tag and `<div>` tag isn't supposed to contain the `<head>`. It is used for titles and metadata only.
<|end|>


