```jsx
import { render, fireEvent } from "@testing-library/react";
import App from "./App";

test("renders Title", () => {
  const { getByText } = render(<App />);
  const textElement = getByText(/Congratulations, You've Made it!/i);
  expect(textElement).toBeInTheDocument();
});

test("check button click changes animation", () => {
  const { getByText } = render(<App />);
  const buttonElement = getByText(/Celebrate!/i);
  fireEvent.click(buttonElement);
  const textElement = getByText(/Congratulations, You've Made it!/i);
  expect(textElement).toHaveStyle("animation-name");
});
```

Please note that this won't test animation specifically since it changes rapidly and its difference cannot easily be caught. You also need to mock Math.random to make it predictable for the test environment.

