Develop a Java-based method that computes and exhibits the Fibonacci numerical sequence up to a user-defined integer threshold while ensuring optimized performance and accurate results.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is the Java program to compute Fibonacci numerical sequence.

```Java
public class Fibonacci {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int threshold = 10;  // Define your threshold here
        int[] fibSequence = computeFibonacciSequence(threshold);

        if (fibSequence == null) {
            System.out.println("Threshold should be a positive integer.");
            return;
        }

        // Print the Fibonacci sequence 
        System.out.println("The Fibonacci sequence up to " + threshold + " is: ");
        for (int i = 0; i < fibSequence.length; i++) {
            System.out.print(fibSequence[i] + " ");
        }
    }

    // Method to compute Fibonacci sequence
    public static int[] computeFibonacciSequence(int threshold) {
        if (threshold <= 0) {
            return null;
        }

        int[] fibSequence = new int[threshold];
        fibSequence[0] = 0;
        if (threshold == 1) {
            return fibSequence;
        }

        fibSequence[1] = 1;

        for(int i = 2; i < threshold; i++) {
            fibSequence[i] = fibSequence[i - 1] + fibSequence[i - 2];
        }

        return fibSequence;
    }
}

```
This Java program takes a user-defined threshold to compute and print the Fibonacci sequence up to that number. It takes an iterative approach (instead of recursion) to ensure better performance in terms of time complexity. Also, we use an array to store the Fibonacci sequence for accuracy of results.

Please note: In practical terms, the size of the Fibonacci sequence that can be accurately represented will depend on the maximum size of the integer data type you're using. After some point, the numbers of the Fibonacci sequence will exceed the maximum size limit, causing overflow issues. In such a scenario, you may need to use data types capable of storing larger numbers (like BigInteger in Java).
<|end|>


