Formulate a segment of JavaScript coding language, purposed for determining the product of standalone digits nestled within a preselected whole number, particularly represented by the figure of 847.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is a simple JavaScript code snippet that does exactly what you described - it calculates the product of all the digits in the number 847.

```javascript
let num = 847;
let product = 1;

while (num > 0) {
    product *= num % 10;
    num = Math.floor(num / 10);
}

console.log(product);
```

This JavaScript code first sets a variable `num` to the required number 847 and another variable `product` to 1 to hold the result. Then there is a while loop that runs as long as the `num` is more than zero. Within the loop, we calculate the product using `%` operator (which gives the remainder of a division operation, in this case, it gives the last digit of the number). Then we update `num` to the integer part of the division of `num` by 10, effectively removing the last digit from the number. The loop runs until all digits have been processed. Then it prints the result, which is the product of all the digits.
<|end|>


