i have a dataset that uses the format '1998:q1' however this does not recognise as a temporal variable in vega lite. Is there a way to convert this in to the format 1998/01 and repeat this for the whole dataset?
[link to dataset](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/GeorgeRobbin/GeorgeRobbin.github.io/main/Book1.csv)
Current format:

| Date | 
| ---- | 
| 1998:Q1 | 
| 1998:Q2 | 


Desired format:

| Date | 
| ---- | 
| 1998/01 | 
| 1998/04 | 


tried

df['Date']=pd.to_datetime(df['Date'],format = '%Y%M')
<|end|>
<|asst|>
In Python, using Pandas, you could process the 'Date' column to convert each 'Qx' into the corresponding month number. A function can be written to extract the year and quarter values and convert them into your desired format. Here's an approach:

```python
import pandas as pd

# Read the dataframe
df = pd.read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/GeorgeRobbin/GeorgeRobbin.github.io/main/Book1.csv')

# Function to convert 'Qx' into month:
def convert_quarter_to_month(date):
    year, quarter = date.split(':')
    if quarter == 'Q1':
        month = '01'
    elif quarter == 'Q2':
        month = '04'
    elif quarter == 'Q3':
        month = '07'
    elif quarter == 'Q4':
        month = '10'
    return '{}/{}'.format(year, month)

# Apply the function to each date in the 'Date' column
df['Date'] = df['Date'].apply(convert_quarter_to_month)

print(df)
```

This script will read your CSV file and apply the conversion function to each date in the 'Date' column. After running it, dates like '1998:Q1' will be '1998/01', '1998:Q2' will be '1998/04', and so on.
<|end|>


