Construct a JavaScript function that identifies the most concise shared ending substring within a pair of supplied text strings. Consider these inputs: "destruction" and "auction".
<|end|>
<|asst|>
You are basically being asked to find the longest common suffix between two input strings.

Here's a simple solution written in JavaScript:

```javascript
function findCommonSuffix(str1, str2) {
  let index1 = str1.length - 1;
  let index2 = str2.length - 1;
  let result = '';

  while(index1 >= 0 && index2 >= 0) {
    if(str1.charAt(index1) === str2.charAt(index2)) {
      result = str1.charAt(index1) + result;
      index1--;
      index2--;
    } else {
      break;
    }
  }

  return result;
}

console.log(findCommonSuffix("destruction", "auction"));  // outputs 'uction'
```

This function operates by starting from the end of both strings and working backwards. When the characters at the current position in both strings match, that character is added to the beginning of the result string. The function continues to do this until it encounters differing characters in the two strings, or until it has processed all characters from one or both strings.

By doing this, the function effectively finds the longest common ending substring (or suffix) shared by the two input strings.
<|end|>


