<|asst|>
Here's my solution:

```java
import java.util.*;
import java.lang.*;

class Pair<T1, T2> {
    T1 first;
    T2 second;

    public Pair(T1 first, T2 second) {
        this.first = first;
        this.second = second;
    }
}

class Solution {
    /**
    returns encoded string by shifting every character by a random integer between 1 and 5.
     */
    public Pair<String, int[]> encodeShift(String s) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        Random random = new Random();

        int[] shifts = new int[s.length()];

        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++){
            int shift = random.nextInt(5) + 1; // generate random shift between 1 and 5
            shifts[i] = shift;
            char c = (char)(s.charAt(i) + shift); // add the shift to current char.
            sb.append(c);
        }

        return new Pair<>(sb.toString(), shifts); // return Pair of encoded string and array of shifts
    }

    /**
    takes as input string encoded with encodeShift function.
    Returns decoded string.
     */
    public String decodeShift(String s, int[] shifts) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++){
            char c = (char)(s.charAt(i) - shifts[i]); // subtract the shift from the current char
            sb.append(c);
        }

        return sb.toString(); // return the decoded string.
    }
}

```

In this implementation, each character of the input string is shifted right by a random number of positions between 1 and 5, including both ends. The random shifts are stored in an array. The encoded string and the array of shifts are returned as a pair.

In the decodeShift function, each character of the input string is shifted left by the corresponding shift stored in the shifts array, thereby retrieving the original string. Please note that if your original string contains special characters, they may be transformed into non-readable characters after encoding and decoding. This could be improved by only applying the shift on printable characters and leaving special characters untouched.
<|end|>


