Create a dictionary based on the elements from list x and their combined occurrence count in both list x and list y. Then, for every key-value pair in the dictionary, find the pair with the highest value. If there are multiple entries with the highest value, return them all.

list x: [7, 12, 17, 22, 27]
list y: [2, 7, 12, 17, 22]
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is a Python solution to approach this problem.

```python
# Define lists
x = [7, 12, 17, 22, 27]
y = [2, 7, 12, 17, 22]

# Combine lists into one
combined = x + y

# Create a dictionary based off the combined list
dict_count = {i: combined.count(i) for i in x}

# Find highest value in the dictionary
highest_value = max(dict_count.values())

# Find keys with highest value
keys_with_highest_value = [k for k, v in dict_count.items() if v == highest_value]

# Print keys
print(keys_with_highest_value)
```

When you run this programme, it will print: [7, 12, 17, 22] which are the elements that appear in both lists x and y and their combined occurrence count is the highest in this case.
<|end|>


