Write a for loop in JavaScript that prints Fibonacci sequence up to the nth number, where n is an integer input by user. Your program should include exception handling to ensure that the user inputs a positive integer.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here's a solution using JavaScript:

```javascript
function fibonacci(n) {
    // exception handling for wrong input
    if (typeof n !== 'number' || n < 1 ){
        console.log('Error: Please input a positive integer.')
    } else {
        if(n === 1) {
            console.log(0)
        } else if(n === 2) {
            console.log('0\n1')
        } else {
            let num1 = 0, num2 = 1, next, counter = 3;
            console.log('0\n1');
            while(counter <= n) {
                next = num1 + num2;
                num1 = num2;
                num2 = next;
                console.log(next);
                counter++;
            }
        }
    }
}

fibonacci(10);  // replace 10 with user input
```

Before the loop begins, we check if the input is a number and it is positive. If not, we print error message. We check if the requested quantity of numbers is 1 or 2 because these cases are slightly different - the loop won't be started in these cases because the sequence always starts with 0 and 1, you just have to print it. 

If the user has requested more than 2 numbers, we print the first two outside the loop, then start a loop that will proceed until it has printed the requested quantity of numbers. Inside the loop, we calculate the next number as a sum of the last two numbers, move the last two numbers one step forward and print the next number.
<|end|>


