2. Join users and orders, handling nulls:

```sql
SELECT u.*, o.* 
FROM users u 
LEFT JOIN orders o ON u.user_id = o.user_id 
WHERE u.user_id = 2;
```

With the LEFT JOIN, we make sure all data from the "users" table will be shown and, in cases where there are no matching entries in the "orders" table, null values will be returned.

3. Aggregate total order amounts, in descending order, along with other user details:

```sql
SELECT u.*, SUM(o.order_amount) AS total_order_amount 
FROM users u 
LEFT JOIN orders o ON u.user_id = o.user_id 
WHERE u.user_id = 2
GROUP BY u.user_id
ORDER BY total_order_amount DESC;
```
  
