Create a MySQL query to join two tables together and filter the results by a given column.
Table1:

id|name
1|Bob
2|Anne

Table2:
id|age
1|26
2|25
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here's a simple MySQL query that will join these two tables together on the id field, and where you can filter the results by a given column:

```SQL
SELECT t1.id, t1.name, t2.age
FROM Table1 t1
INNER JOIN Table2 t2 ON t1.id = t2.id
WHERE t2.age > 25;
```

This query will return a result set with each user's id, name, and age where the age is more than 25. You can change what you are comparing to and the value (in this case, 'age' and '25') to filter on different criteria. Or you can delete the WHERE row to simply join the two tables based on ID.
