<|asst|>
Sure, here is a simple example of a membership system in PHP. This example includes a login and register system, and it uses MySQL as a database.

```php
<?php 

$host = 'localhost';
$db   = 'test_db';
$user = 'root';
$pass = '';
$charset = 'utf8mb4';

$dsn = "mysql:host=$host;dbname=$db;charset=$charset";
$opt = [
    PDO::ATTR_ERRMODE            => PDO::ERRMODE_EXCEPTION,
    PDO::ATTR_DEFAULT_FETCH_MODE => PDO::FETCH_ASSOC,
    PDO::ATTR_EMULATE_PREPARES   => false,
];
$pdo = new PDO($dsn, $user, $pass, $opt);


// Register user
if(isset($_POST['register'])){
   $username = $_POST['username'];
   $password = password_hash($_POST['password'], PASSWORD_BCRYPT);

   $sql = "INSERT INTO users(username, password) VALUES(?, ?)";
   $stmt= $pdo->prepare($sql);
   $stmt->execute([$username, $password]);
   echo "Registration Successful!";
}

// User login 
if(isset($_POST['login'])){
   $username = $_POST['username'];
   $password = $_POST['password'];

   $sql = "SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = ?";
   $stmt= $pdo->prepare($sql);
   $stmt->execute([$username]);
   $user = $stmt->fetch();

   if($user && password_verify($password, $user['password'])){
      echo "Login Successful!";
   }else{
      echo "Username or password is incorrect.";
   }
}

?>

<!-- A simple form -->
<form method="POST" action="membership.php">
  Username: <input type="text" name="username" required><br>
  Password: <input type="password" name="password" required><br>
  <input type="submit" name="register" value="Register">
  <input type="submit" name="login" value="Login">
</form>
```

This is just the basic system and doesn't have any security measures in place nor any user input validation/sanitation, so be sure to add these if you intend to use it! It doesn't have frontend interfaces for the user interactions nor error messages for the end user.

You will need to replace the database configuration according to your database and you need to create a 'users' table in your 'test_db' database with 'username' and 'password' fields. 

In the form, when a user chooses "Register", it will register the user with the provided username and password, and when user chooses "Login", it will login the user.
