Develop a SQL query that showcases a comprehensive tabular output illustrating the quantity of records corresponding to every individual month throughout an entire year.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
To provide an SQL query that satisfies your request, an example of a table structure (suppose we have a table named 'Records' and it has a 'Date' field) and SQL dialect must be assumed. Here is an example of a standard SQL query for overall types of SQL (PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQL Server, Oracle):

```sql
SELECT 
    MONTH(Date) AS Month,
    COUNT(*) AS Quantity
FROM 
    Records
WHERE
    YEAR(Date) = 2021
GROUP BY 
    MONTH(Date)
ORDER BY
    MONTH(Date);
```

This would return a result such as:
```
Month    |    Quantity
-------------------- 
1        |    45
2        |    60
3        |    50
4        |    70
5        |    80
6        |    100
7        |    95
8        |    100
9        |    120
10       |    90
11       |    80
12       |    70
```

This query calculates the number of records for each month of the year 2021. If you want for an entire year, you can remove the YEAR(Date) = 2021 condition and group by both YEAR(Date) and MONTH(Date). 

Always remember not all syntax works on all types of SQL, you need to adjust the command according to your managing system. 
This query is written on the assumption that SQL dialect is MySQL. Changes may be required if it's run on other SQL based systems like Oracle, MS SQL, or PostgreSQL. Please make sure to replace the table name and column names as per your database table.
