Im trying to play the Windows Hardware Sounds using a C#(.net) Console Application. But I can only find how to play the beep sound using SystemSounds.
I tried to use SystemSounds for this, but it can only do the Beep Sound using

SystemSounds.Exclamation.Play();
<|end|>
<|asst|>
SystemSounds class is pretty limited, it only provides the following system sounds:

- Asterisk
- Beep
- Hand
- Exclamation
- Question

If you need other specific Windows sounds, you will have to play them manually. These sounds are usually stored as .wav files in the Windows Media directory.

You can use System.Media.SoundPlayer class to play these .wav files:

```csharp
using System.Media;

SoundPlayer player = new SoundPlayer(@"C:\Windows\Media\Windows Notify System Generic.wav");
player.Play();
```

Replace `@"C:\Windows\Media\Windows Notify System Generic.wav"` with the path to the .wav file you want to play. Make sure your application has the proper permissions to access these files.

It's important to note that the location and set of these sound files may change with different versions of Windows, so this solution may not work in all environments.

SoundPlayer can also play a .wav file from a Stream, so if you need a more robust solution, you can embed these sounds into your application as resources.

If you want to use the current Windows scheme sounds, you'll have to query the registry for them. They're located under `HKEY_CURRENT_USER\AppEvents\Schemes\Apps\.Default`. You have then to use the `System.Media.SoundPlayer` to play the .wav file specified in the registry.
<|end|>


