Use the Beautiful Soup module in Python to parse this HTML: '<html><head><title>Title of the webpage</title></head><body><p>This is a test paragraph.</p><div>This is a div</div></body></html>'. Print the text of the paragraph tag and the div tag. Also, find and print the total number of 'i's in the text content.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
You first need to import the Beautiful Soup module using `from bs4 import BeautifulSoup`. Then, you can parse the HTML using the `BeautifulSoup()` function. You can access the text of the paragraph tag and the div tag using Beautiful Soup’s `.text` attribute. To find and print the total number of 'i's in the text content, you can use the `str.count()` method. Here's how you can do it:

```python
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

html = '<html><head><title>Title of the webpage</title></head><body><p>This is a test paragraph.</p><div>This is a div</div></body></html>'

# Parse the HTML
soup = BeautifulSoup(html, 'html.parser')

# Find the paragraph tag
parag = soup.find('p').text
print('Text of the paragraph tag:', parag)

# Find the div tag
div = soup.find('div').text
print('Text of the div tag:', div)

# Find and print total no. of 'i's in the text content
total_i = parag.count('i') + div.count('i')
print('Total number of "i"s in the text content:', total_i)
```

This code will output:
```python
Text of the paragraph tag: This is a test paragraph.
Text of the div tag: This is a div
Total number of "i"s in the text content: 4
```
Note that the count includes both the 'i' in "This" and the 'i' in "div".
<|end|>


