Can you validate the following complex aspects of the Python programming language?
A) Its ability to facilitate automatic garbage collection
B) Its flexibility to integrate seamlessly with other programming languages and software component object model systems like C, C++, COM, ActiveX, CORBA, and Java.
C) Both of the above abilities are inherent features of Python.
D) Python lacks all of the above mentioned capabilities.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
A) Validate: Python does indeed facilitate automatic garbage collection. It has a built-in garbage collector, which recycles all the unused memory and frees the memory and makes it available to the heap space.

B) Validate: Python provides the CTypes library which allows for seamless C integration, and there is also a built-in support for C and C++ extensions. Python can also be used in various other languages and systems like Java (via Jython), .NET (via IronPython), and can interact with COM, ActiveX, and CORBA objects (via win32com and pythonnet libraries respectively). 

C) Validate: Both of these capabilities are inherent features of Python. They are built into the Python Standard Library or can be facilitated through Python's simplistic, flexible syntax and through certain Python packages.

D) Invalidate: Python does not lack the above-mentioned capabilities. It supports automatic garbage collection and integration with several languages and object model systems, as stated earlier.
<|end|>


