it keeps giving me an error every time I run it and it's always a different error after I change the code
This is my method that I found, Im coding this in the latest version of node.js and discord.js

const { Client, Intents } = require('discord.js');
const fs = require('fs');

// Create a new client
const client = new Client({
  intents: new Intents(Intents.ALL),
});


My error for this is TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'ALL')
I tried this too

const client = new Client({
  intents: new Intents([
    'GUILDS',
    'GUILD_MESSAGES',
    'MESSAGE_CONTENT',
    'GUILD_MEMBERS',
  ]),
});


And still it gives me an error TypeError: Intents is not a constructor
I don't know any other way to fix, this can someone help me?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Your usage of `Intents` is outdated, and therefore incorrect for the current version of `discord.js`.

`Intents.ALL` has been deprecated and should not be used. As well as that, `Intents` aren't constructed by passing an array of string, but with a bitfield or array of bitwise flags.

These could be the reasons why you are encountering such errors. The method of how Intents are defined was changed in discord.js version 13.

The correct way, as of discord.js v13.1.0, is shown below.

```js
const { Client, Intents } = require('discord.js');

const client = new Client({
    intents: [
        Intents.FLAGS.Guilds,
        Intents.FLAGS.GuildMessages,
        Intents.FLAGS.MessageContent,
        Intents.FLAGS.GuildMembers,
    ]
});
```

Keep in mind that `MessageContent` is not a valid intent, you may want `MessageContent` if you're planning to content of messages. You can find a list of intents [here](https://discordjs.guide/popular-topics/intents.html).

Check the version of discord.js you're using since the Intents have been introduced in discord.js v12 and have seen changes in v13. You can check the version you're using by running `npm list discord.js` in your console.

The error `TypeError: Intents is not a constructor` happened because you tried to use the `Intents` as a constructor function, but it's not designed to be used that way. It's an object that contains properties representing different categories of events your bot can respond to. For each category of events you want your bot to respond to, you should include the corresponding property from the `Intents` object in the array you pass to the `Client` constructor.
<|end|>


