In HTML, the `<` and `>` characters are reserved for marking up HTML tags. To display these characters as text, you must use character entities:

- `&lt;` for `<`
- `&gt;` for `>`

So your `Func<int, int>` should be written as `Func&lt;int, int&gt;` in the HTML. The final HTML code for your section would look like:

```html
<pre>
    PrimeCalc calc = new PrimeCalc();
    Func&lt;int, int&gt; del = calc.GetNextPrime;
</pre>
```

This would correctly display as:

```csharp
PrimeCalc calc = new PrimeCalc();
Func<int, int> del = calc.GetNextPrime;
``` in a webpage.
