It seems like the Neurotec libraries are not available on the Maven Central. You might have to install them manually to your local Maven repository:

Follow these steps:

1: Look for the jar file on the Neurotec website or anywhere else on the internet and download it.

2: If you find the jar file, move it to your local directory, something like "`C:\lib`".

Now, you need to install this jar to your local repository manually, here is a command to do this:

```
mvn install:install-file -Dfile=<Path-to-File> -DgroupId=com.neurotec -DartifactId=neurotec-media -Dversion=12.3.0.0 -Dpackaging=jar
```

You should replace `<Path-to-File>` with your actual path to jar file. Repeat the same for the other jar file too.

NOTE: if there is a problem in getting the jar file, you might have to contact the vendor or check if they have a different repository or another way of getting those libraries.

If the vendor (Neurotec) provide their own maven repository, you will need to add that repository to your `pom.xml` file like this:

```xml
<repositories>
    <repository>
        <id>Neurotec</id>
        <url>http://url-to-the-vendor's-repository</url>
    </repository>
</repositories>
```

When it's done, your Maven project will have access to the necessary resources. It will know where to check for the Neurotec dependencies when you run `mvn clean install`.
