<|asst|>
The negative score in cross-validation is usually occurring when the metric is Mean Squared Error (MSE) or any other error measurement metric where lower value is better score. 

Scikit-learn’s cross_val_score() function by default calculates score, where higher score indicates better model. But in case of error measurement metrics like MSE, lower value indicates better model. So, to make it consistent with the cross_val_score() function where higher score is better, scikit-learn negates the output. That’s why you are seeing negative value for MSE. The way to interpret this will be to take the absolute values before comparing models, as a higher error means a worse model.
