list_2 = [4, 2, 6]
print(concat_sort_lists(list_1, list_2)) # Expected output: [1, 2, 2, 3, 4, 6]

list_1 = [5, 8, 9]
list_2 = [1, 7, 3]
print(concat_sort_lists(list_1, list_2)) # Expected output: [1, 3, 5, 7, 8, 9]

list_1 = [10, 11, 12]
list_2 = [10, 11, 12]
print(concat_sort_lists(list_1, list_2)) # Expected output: [10, 10, 11, 11, 12, 12]
```

This function runs with a time complexity of O(n log n) due to the sorted method, where n is the total number of elements in the combined list.
