```python
# Input list of string sequences
list_strings = ["12.1 10.2 6.3 5.4", "7.2 3.4", "8.9 1.2 4.6"]

#Create a single list of floating point numbers
list_floats = [float(i) for sublist in list_strings for i in sublist.split()]
print(list_floats)
```
This script works by first iterating over the items of the outer list, `list_strings`. For each string, it applies the `split` method which by default splits the string by any whitespace into a list of smaller strings. Then, it iterates over this list of strings, converts each string into a floating point number using the `float` function, and finally appends each number to the result list, `list_floats`.

Please, run this script in an environment where Python is installed or in an online compiler and you should get this output:
