Create a Nodejs program to print a Fibonacci sequence of length n.
5
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Below is a Nodejs program that prints a Fibonacci sequence of specified length:

```javascript
const fibonacci = (n) => {

  if(n <= 0) {
    return 'The length of the sequence should be greater than zero.'
  }
  
  let fibSequence = [0, 1];

  if (n === 1) {
    return fibSequence[0];
  }

  if (n === 2) {
    return fibSequence;
  }

  for (let i = 2; i < n; i++) {
    let nextNum = fibSequence[i-1] + fibSequence[i-2];
    fibSequence.push(nextNum);
  }

  return fibSequence;
}

console.log(fibonacci(5));
```
You can run the code using Node.js and passing the length of the sequence you want to generate as an argument to the `fibonacci` function. This code will print the first 5 numbers of the Fibonacci sequence in the console.
