Construct a JavaScript code snippet that outputs the exact present date and time in the following format: "Wednesday, November 20, 2019 12:00:00 AM GMT+0530", ensuring effective use of the Date object and its methods.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is a JavaScript code snippet that uses the built-in `Date` object to obtain the present date and time.

```javascript
var current_date =  new Date();
var days = ["Sunday","Monday","Tuesday","Wednesday","Thursday","Friday","Saturday"];
var months = ["January", "February", "March", "April", "May", "June", "July", "August", "September", "October", "November", "December"];
var date_str = days[current_date.getDay()] + ', ' + 
               months[current_date.getMonth()] + ' ' + 
               current_date.getDate().toString().padStart(2, '0') + ', ' + 
               current_date.getFullYear() + ' ' + 
               current_date.getHours().toString().padStart(2, '0') + ':' + 
               current_date.getMinutes().toString().padStart(2, '0') + ':' + 
               current_date.getSeconds().toString().padStart(2, '0') + ' ' +
               'GMT' + (-(current_date.getTimezoneOffset() / 60)).toString().padStart(2, '0') + '00';

console.log(date_str);
```

Please note that the timezone offset is in minutes and negative of what you may expect. So, when we divide by 60, we get GMT+05:30 as GMT+5300 instead of GMT-5300.

Also, be aware that getTimezoneOffset returns the offset in minutes with positive number for timezones that are behind UTC and negative number for timezones that are ahead of UTC which we convert to the required standard and string format accordingly.

Please also note that this code snippet will output the current date and time of where the server that the script runs on is physically located or what timezone is set for the server environment and may not correspond to GMT+0530 (India Standard Time) if it's run somewhere else.

Ensure to consider these dynamics when implementing your final solution. This script offers the general approach to achieving the described format.
<|end|>


