Devise a code segment in the Java programming language that meticulously identifies the mathematic peak value among a series of integers encapsulated within an array structure, given this specified integer sequence: [1, 4, 6, 8, 9, 4, 2].
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Sure, here's a simple Java method that accomplishes this:
```java
public int findPeak(int[] nums) {
    int max = nums[0];

    for(int i=1; i<nums.length; i++){
        if(nums[i] > max) {
            max = nums[i];
        }
    }

    return max;
}
```

You would run it with the following invocation:
```java
int[] nums = {1, 4, 6, 8, 9, 4, 2};
int result = findPeak(nums);
System.out.println("Peak Value is: " + result);
```
This method simply iterates over the given array and keeps track of the maximum value it encounters. The maximum value will be the peak value.
<|end|>


