How do I get it to work with my project?

[http://ajax.asp.net/](http://ajax.asp.net/)

[http://www.codeplex.com/AjaxControlToolkit/](http://www.codeplex.com/AjaxControlToolkit/)
<|end|>
<|asst|>
To use AJAX in your project, you will need to follow these steps:

1. Download the AJAX Control Toolkit from the CodePlex site. Unzip the downloaded file. Remember the location where you extracted the files.

2. Open your project in Visual Studio.

3. Right-click on the Toolbox panel, and then click on 'Choose Items...'.

4. In the 'Choose Toolbox Items' window, go to '.NET Framework Components' tab and click on 'Browse...'.

5. Navigate to the location where you extracted the AJAX Control Toolkit. Choose the 'AjaxControlToolkit.dll' file, and click on 'Open'.

6. Now, you can see the AJAX Control Toolkit in the Toolbox. You can always drag and drop any controls into your ASP.NET web page.

7. After adding the AJAX toolkit to your project, you will need to reference it in your Site.Master page or your specific ASP.Net page in order to use the controls. For this, add the following line to your page:

```html
<%@ Register Assembly="AjaxControlToolkit" Namespace="AjaxControlToolkit" TagPrefix="ajaxToolkit" %>
```

8. Now, you can use AJAX toolkit controls in your project. Remember to refer to the AJAX tab in the toolbox and also the official documentation to understand how to use specific controls.

Keep in mind that to take full advantage of AJAX, you should have a knowledge of C# or Visual Basic to handle server-side functions and also Javascript for client-side handling. AJAX controls mostly generate client-side code automatically, but some complex cases require manual handling of client-side custom scripts.
<|end|>


