I have a code for creating QLDB Ledgers on AWS. It works well but I can't find any documentation about this limitation.

Amazon.QLDB.Model.LimitExceededException: 'Exceeded the limit of 5 active ledgers'


I have 5 ledgers within an account/region. If I try to create a new one from the aws console I get this error message: "Error: failed to create ledger."
In my company we plan to create as many ledgers as customer amount we have. How can I make this simple?
Thanks
Regards
<|end|>
<|asst|>
The maximum number of ledgers that you can create in a single AWS account/region is 5. If you want to create many ledgers, you will need to manage this limit. 

Here are some possible options:

1. Request an Increase: You could attempt to get this limit increased by creating an AWS Support case. AWS will typically only increase the limit if they're given a valid use case, but it's definitely worth a try.

2. Use Multiple AWS Accounts/Regions: Since the limit is per account per region, you could create additional AWS accounts or use more AWS regions to have more ledgers.

3. Design Changes: Perhaps you could decrease the number of ledgers you need by reorganizing your data. For example, rather than needing a ledger for each customer, you may be able to use tables or partitions within a ledger to separate customer data.

Remember that every design decision might have consequences and, in some cases, limitations.

Also, consider the cost efficiency. Having many ledgers might not be the best way economically because AWS QLDB charges you based on the read/write IO and storage. It's better to consult this with your architecture team or even AWS support.
  
Refer to AWS Quotas documentation for further understanding of these limits: [AWS Service Quotas](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/aws_service_limits.html)

Lastly, always ensure that your approach complies with AWS' best practices for security and compliance.
<|end|>


