I'm really new to .NET, and I still didn't get the hang about how configuration files work.

Every time I search on Google about it I get results about web.config, but I'm writing a Windows Forms application.

I figured out that I need to use the System.Configuration namespace, but the documentation isn't helping.

How do I define that my configuration file is XYZ.xml? Or does it have a "default" name for the configuration file? I still didn't get that.

Also, how do I define a new section? Do I really need to create a class which inherits from ConfigurationSection?

I would like to just have a configuration file with some values like this:


<MyCustomValue>1</MyCustomValue>
<MyCustomPath>C:\Some\Path\Here</MyCustomPath>



Is there a simple way to do it? Can you explain in a simple way how to read and write from/to a simple configuration file?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Configuration files in .NET (e.g., app.config, web.config) help developers to specify some environment specific details (like connection strings, app settings, etc.) which can be modified without modifying the actual code.

For a Windows Forms application, .NET automatically looks for a file named yourProgramName.exe.config in the same directory as your app, where "yourProgramName" is the assembly (executable) name of your program.

If you want to use such a file, you can add it in Visual Studio by right-clicking your project (not the solution) in the Solution Explorer, then select Add -> New Item, and pick "Application Configuration File". It will create an app.config file, which becomes yourProgramName.exe.config when you compile.

The default structure of an app.config file is:

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<configuration>
    <startup> 
        <supportedRuntime version="v4.0" sku=".NETFramework,Version=v4.7.2" />
    </startup>
</configuration>
```

You can add custom configuration settings in appSettings section like this:

```xml
<configuration>
  <appSettings>
    <add key="MyCustomValue" value="1" />
    <add key="MyCustomPath" value="C:\Some\Path\Here" /> 
  </appSettings>
</configuration>
```

And then read these settings in your application like this:

```csharp
var myCustomValue = ConfigurationManager.AppSettings["MyCustomValue"];
var myCustomPath = ConfigurationManager.AppSettings["MyCustomPath"];
```

Make sure you have reference to `System.Configuration` in your project and in your using declarations. 

Keep in mind that app.config file is a static file and it is not supposed to be changed at runtime. If you want to read/write configuration data at runtime then the better option might be XML Serialization or using a simple Database.
<|end|>


