I like to sell uncovered put options, using my valuation of the company as the strike price. I'm looking for a tool that takes stock identifier and strike price as input and outputs the optimal expiration date, i.e. one that has the highest ratio of option price to days until expiration. Can anybody suggest anything?
<|end|>
<|asst|>
You're asking for a highly specialized tool and I'm not sure there's anything commercially available that would directly fit your precise requirements. Most trading platforms like ThinkOrSwim or Interactive Brokers would allow you to scan and sort option chains based on various criteria - however, it would mostly revolve around implied volatility, volume, open interest, and spreads. 

However, if you are programming-savvy, you might be able to utilize an API (Application Programming Interface) service from a brokerage like Interactive Brokers or TD Ameritrade to create your own, custom software tool that could do this task. 

You should reach out to your broker and ask them if they have such a tool in their platform. Also find out if they have an API you are allowed to use free of charge, in case you wish to build your own program. Alternatively, you could hire a programmer to create such a tool, but be aware of the potential cost and risks (including security) associated with this solution.

To evaluate the risk/reward ratio (the option price to days until expiration ratio), you might also need historical data and options pricing models like Black-Scholes or Binomial Tree models. Please be aware that historical data usually come with a cost, or can be unreliable if gotten for free.

Last but not least, beware of the risks involved in selling uncovered put options. If the stock price crashes, your losses could be substantial. Make sure you understand the risks of being an uncovered writer and that you're financially able to bear those risks.
<|end|>


