<|asst|>
Creating a trail or motion effect behind SVG shape actually requires some knowledge of CSS or JavaScript. There is no build-in way to do this purely in SVG. The idea behind creating a motion trail effect involves making several copies of the shape with slightly different positions and colors, then animating these copies over time to create the appearance of motion. Below is a simple CSS animation that creates a trailing effect:

```html
<style>
@keyframes animate {
    0% { transform: translateX(0); opacity: 1; }
    100% { transform: translateX(20px); opacity: 0; }
}

.svg-shape {
    animation: animate 1s linear infinite;
}
