Formulate a Java program that computes the product of the digits of an assigned number.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Here is a simple program in Java that can fulfill your request. 

This program takes an integer as an input and then separates its digits, multiplying them together and finally providing the product of the digits.

```java
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main
{
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.println("Enter a number: ");
        int num = scanner.nextInt(); 
        int product = 1;
        while(num != 0) {
            product = product * (num % 10);
            num = num / 10;
        }
        System.out.println("Product of the digits: " + product);
    }
}
```
To run the program, you just need to:

1. Paste the code into a Java compiler 
2. Run the program 
3. When prompted, input the number whose digits you wish to multiply together. 

The program then will print out the product of the digits in your number.
